            .</p>
               <p>For the Prosecution, MR ALLEY.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200217-152-person1464">
                  JOSEPH 
                  PARKIN
               <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1464" type="surname" value="PARKIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1464" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18200217-152-viclabel882" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18200217-152-crimeloc883">George, public-house, George-yard, Whitechapel</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-crimeloc883" type="placeName" value="George, public-house, George-yard, Whitechapel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-crimeloc883" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-152-off880 t18200217-152-crimeloc883"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-152-victim1463 t18200217-152-viclabel882"></join>. On the 29th of October the prisoner came to my house with his brother (not Samuel). He asked me to give him cash for a bill, which I produce? it had about a fortnight to run - the acceptance was on it at the time. I said I could not cash it unless his other brother endorsed it. He took it away, and brought it back with the name</p>
               <p>"
               <persName id="t18200217-152-person1465">
                  Samuel 
                  Welldon
               <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1465" type="surname" value="Welldon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1465" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-152-person1465" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            " endorsed on it. I then gave him 10 l., and wrote to his brother, whose acceptance it purported to be; I advanced him in all 35 l. in goods and money. On the 19th of December it was due, but was not paid.</p>
               <p>Q. Was the prisoner afterwards apprehended - A. Yes, and said if he had had the full amount of the bill his brother would have paid it. His brother refused to attend here.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200217-152-person1466">
